summary: sub_404200 is a thin wrapper that initializes a local variable to 0x1d and then tail‑calls sub_404020, performing no other observable work.
details: The function sets a stack variable var_8 to the constant 0x1d but never uses it before the tail call.
It immediately transfers execution to sub_404020 via a tail call (call:0x404020).
unknowns: The purpose of the local variable var_8 and whether sub_404020 uses it.
The actual behavior of sub_404020, which appears to jump to a nullptr placeholder.
